FBIS4-3861 "drchi080_a_94025" FBIS-CHI-94-080 Daily Report 23 Apr 1994 INTERNATIONAL AFFAIRS General Albania Ratifies NATO's Partnership for Peace Albania Ratifies NATO's Partnership for Peace OW2304194794 Beijing XINHUA in English 1627 GMT 23 Apr 94 OW2304194794 Beijing XINHUA English BFN [Text] Tirana, April 23 (XINHUA) -- The Albanian parliament today ratified a document on Partnership for Peace with NATO as a step toward better relations with West European countries. In February, Albanian President Sali Berisha signed the document with NATO Secretary General Manfred Worner in Brussels and later submitted it to the People's Assembly for approval. Before the parliament convened over the weekend, the president told the lawmakers that ratification of the agreement was an important step toward new cooperation with NATO. He stressed that it was also part of Albania's efforts to obtain full membership in NATO. The document provides that Albania and NATO will cooperate in peacekeeping missions, rescue operations and military exercises. No further details were available.
